title: 30-Minute Bodyweight Workout
description:

channelDescription:
The brand you know and love as POPSUGAR is now PS, and our popular workout series (including Class Fitsugar, Dance Fitsugar, and Breathe Fitsugar) are now united under a single brand: PS Fit.

PS has long dominated the fitness space as the No. 1 source for free at-home workouts on YouTube, and that’s not changing. We will continue to create workouts for every fitness level, including no-equipment exercises, HIIT workouts, yoga flows, and more. 

On PS Fit, you’ll find videos ranging from five to 60 minutes in length. You can choose to exercise specific body parts and select the level of intensity that works for you. Maybe you want to combine your cardio with dance via a salsa, ’90s pop, or hip-hop workout. If you’re in the mood for stretching, yoga, or meditation, we’ve got you covered there, too. Whatever you choose, you can be confident that all of our workouts are designed and led by knowledgeable and credentialed experts.

comments: It`s great to see the lady on the left doing the modified (easier) versions of some exercises for those who can`t do the "standard" one. Really appreciate it! Thank you

She says at the end, "You can do this workout anytime, anywhere!" And I thought, "as long as you're inside your own place if you're on virus lock down Day 6 like I am, but I get your point." Then they said they would be here for me... and I kinda got a warm fuzzy. For real. Thanks.

I've been so grateful for PopSugar this month as I stockpile some extra fitness time between gym workouts so that I can enjoy the holidays guilt-free. I did this workout today in my kitchen tonight, in my pajamas, while waiting for the royal icing to set on my sugar cookies. I love Taylor's efficient but effective workouts and I know I'll be feeling this a little in my legs tomorrow.

I honestly have been too lazy to workout for the past few months. I just started to do popsugarfitness workout videos a couple of weeks ago and I feel great. I guess I just needed some motivation and believe in myself. my goal is to at least lose close to a hundred pounds by the end of 2020. I know I can do this and never give up on anything. I am just tired of being unfit.

Great total body, arms, legs, abs and bit of cardio + strength mixed in- perfect for a 30minute workout. I also regularly rotate Taylor’s other cardio workout. I love how she uses the usual HIIT breaks fir active recovery abs. Keep the total body cardio, toning 30 minute workouts coming Anna :)
